    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "jsCode": "const validation = $input.first().json;\nconst leadId = $('PostgreSQL').item.json.id;\n\nconst isValid = validation.deliverability === 'DELIVERABLE';\nconst isDisposable = validation.is_disposable_email?.value || false;\n\nreturn {\n  lead_id: leadId,\n  email_valid: isValid && !isDisposable,\n  email_verification_status: validation.deliverability || 'unknown'\n};"
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.code",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        816,
        -96
      ],
      "id": "53f8cbbd-5338-4818-bb55-e62642786e0b",
      "name": "Parse & Update"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "operation": "executeQuery",
        "query": "UPDATE cleaned_leads\nSET \n  email_valid = {{ $json.email_valid }},\n  email_verification_status = '{{ $json.email_verification_status }}'\nWHERE id = {{ $json.lead_id }}\n```\n\n---\n\n## ✅ Benefits of This Approach:\n\n1. **Faster cleaning** - no waiting for API calls\n2. **Better API usage** - batch processing, easier to control rate limits\n3. **Can pause/resume** - stop validation anytime\n4. **Easy monitoring** - see validation progress\n5. **Manual trigger** - validate only when needed\n6. **Priority validation** - validate hot leads first\n\n---\n\n## 🎯 Complete System Flow:\n```\nWorkflow 3: Scrape Leads\n  → staging_leads (raw data)\n  \nWorkflow 4: Clean Data (FAST)\n  → cleaned_leads (email_verification_status = 'pending')\n  \nWorkflow 5: Validate Emails (BATCH - runs hourly)\n  → Updates email_valid = true/false\n  \nWorkflow 6: AI Enrichment\n  → Only enriches leads with email_valid = true",
        "options": {}
      },
